### Test Local LLM API (Ollama)
### Use REST Client extension in VS Code/Cursor to run these.
###
### Prerequisites:
### 1. Ollama running on host: ollama serve (or install from https://ollama.ai)
### 2. Model pulled: ollama pull deepseek-coder
### 3. LLM API running (e.g. Docker): docker-compose up -d llmapi
### 4. .env: LLM_BACKEND=local, LOCAL_LLM_URL=http://host.docker.internal:11434

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5001
@contentType = application/json

###############################################
### 1. Health check (LLM API)
###############################################

### Health
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###############################################
### 2. Generate questions – Local backend (Ollama)
###############################################

### Generate 1 question – Local LLM
POST {{baseUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "topic": "Python programming",
  "level": "easy",
  "n_questions": 5,
  "language": "en",
  "backend": "local"
}

### Generate 2 questions – Local LLM
POST {{baseUrl}}/generate
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "topic": "JavaScript basics",
  "level": "medium",
  "n_questions": 2,
  "language": "en",
  "backend": "local"
}

###############################################
### 3. Moodle generate.php (needs valid quizid + login)
###############################################
### Replace {{quizid}} and optionally {{cmid}} with real IDs from your Moodle quiz.
### You must be logged in (session cookie) or use a tool that sends cookies.

@moodleBase = http://localhost:8080
@quizid = 1
@cmid = 1

### Moodle – Generate questions (local backend)
POST {{moodleBase}}/mod/gamifiedquiz/ajax/generate.php
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

quizid={{quizid}}&cmid={{cmid}}&prompt=Python%20programming&difficulty=easy&count=1
